{"type":"message","id":"f1f7c5af","parentId":"27feef05","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:56:51.736Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jorh5cy7qjte_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 075614\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state:\r\n\r\n1. We have a well-documented research foundation with architecture comparisons, gap-decay synthesis, and compression-causal duality\r\n2. The pending action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n3. Recent pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 075514.md - so we're now on March 24\r\n\r\nThe next logical action is to start implementing the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n1. Check what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement a basic TIC classifier\r\n3. Start measuring invariant/variant patterns\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier that can:\r\n1. Parse recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identify invariant (persistent) vs variant (changing) content\r\n3. Use this to make predictions about next pulse content\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nTIC experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1. We have 17+ pulse logs that can serve as training/test data for invariant/variant classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate Python TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to analyze pulse logs, identify invariant structures vs variant content, and validate against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_sections(content: str) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract named sections from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current = \"header\"\r\n    lines = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n        if line.startswith(\"## \") and not line.startswith(\"###\"):\r\n            if lines:\r\n                sections[current] = \"\\n\".join(lines)\r\n                lines = []\r\n            current = line[3:].strip()\r\n        lines.append(line)\r\n    \r\n    if lines:\r\n        sections[current] = \"\\n\".join(lines)\r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return set(tokens)\r\n\r\ndef jaccard_similarity(set1: set, set2: set) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Jaccard similarity coefficient.\"\"\"\r\n    if not set1 and not set2:\r\n        return 1.0\r\n    if not set1 or not set2:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    intersection = len(set1 & set2)\r\n    union = len(set1 | set2)\r\n    return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(content: str, threshold: float = 0.5) -> list:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify lines/sections as INVARIANT (persistent) or VARIANT (changing).\r\n    Returns list of (classification, line/section) tuples.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    lines = content.split(\"\\n\")\r\n    classifications = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in lines:\r\n        if not line.strip():\r\n            classifications.append((\"variant\", line))  # Empty lines are variant\r\n            continue\r\n            \r\n        # Heuristics for invariant/variant:\r\n        # INVARIANT: file paths, parameter names, version numbers, section headers\r\n        # VARIANT: timestamps, counts, specific values, action items\r\n        \r\n        is_invariant = False\r\n        \r\n        # Check for file paths\r\n        if re.search(r'\\.\\./|\\./[a-z_/]+', line):\r\n            is_invariant = True\r\n        # Check for code blocks (structural)\r\n        elif line.startswith(\"```\"):\r\n            is_invariant = True\r\n        # Check for headers\r\n        elif line.startswith(\"#\") or line.startswith(\"##\"):\r\n            is_invariant = True\r\n        # Check for parameter definitions\r\n        elif re.match(r\"^\\s*[-a-z_]+\\s*[:=]\", line, re.I):\r\n            is_invariant = True\r\n        # Check for timestamps - VARIANT\r\n        elif re.search(r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}|\\d{2}:\\d{2}:\\d{2}\", line):\r\n            is_invariant = False\r\n        # Check for action items\r\n        elif re.search(r\"^\\s*-\\s*\\[\\s*[ x]?\\s*\\]|\\btodo\\b|\\bpending\\b\", line, re.I):\r\n            is_invariant = False\r\n        # Check for counts/numbers\r\n        elif re.search(r\"\\b\\d+\\s+(ms|sec|min|hour|day|iteration)s?\\b\", line):\r\n            is_invariant = False\r\n        else:\r\n            is_invariant = None  # Unknown\r\n            \r\n        classifications.append((\"invariant\" if is_invariant else \"variant\", line))\r\n    \r\n    return classifications\r\n\r\ndef get_pulse_logs(n: int = None) -> list:\r\n    \"\"\"Get n most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True):\r\n        if PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name):\r\n            logs.append(f)\r\n            if n and len(logs) >= n:\r\n                break\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(prev_content: str, invariants: set) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict next pulse content based on invariant structures.\r\n    Returns prediction confidence scores.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    predictions = {\r\n        \"will_contain_invariants\": 0.9, \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 07:56:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353411734}}
